The paper presents algorithms for computing the sumset of two integer sets and multiplying two univariate integer polynomials given by sparse representations. These problems are related to data structures, computational complexity, information theory, computational geometry, and scientific computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.SC (Scientific Computing).
